**Fix cache invalidation/load race condition to prevent serving stale configuration.**

Thread A can read the cached `ConfluenceConnectionSettings` reference at line 126, then Thread B publishes `ConfluenceConfigUpdatedEvent`, triggering `onConfigUpdated()` to clear the cache at line 44. Since Thread A already holds a reference to the old object, the null-check at line 127 fails and the stale settings are returned at line 131. This allows the app to serve outdated Confluence configuration even after an update event.

The race exists because `AtomicReference` is atomic per operation, but the compound check-then-set pattern at lines 126-131 is not synchronized. Synchronize both cache invalidation and loading to ensure all threads see updated configuration immediately after an update event.

<details>
<summary>Proposed fix</summary>

```diff
 public class DatabaseBackedConfluenceConnectionConfig implements ConfluenceConnectionConfig {
+    private final Object settingsLock = new Object();
@@
     public void onConfigUpdated(ConfluenceConfigUpdatedEvent event) {
         log.info("Confluence configuration updated, invalidating cache");
-        cachedSettings.set(null);
+        synchronized (settingsLock) {
+            cachedSettings.set(null);
+        }
     }
@@
     private ConfluenceConnectionSettings getSettings() {
         ConfluenceConnectionSettings settings = cachedSettings.get();
-        if (settings == null) {
-            settings = repository.findConfig();
-            cachedSettings.set(settings);
+        if (settings != null) {
+            return settings;
         }
-        return settings;
+        synchronized (settingsLock) {
+            settings = cachedSettings.get();
+            if (settings == null) {
+                settings = repository.findConfig();
+                cachedSettings.set(settings);
+            }
+            return settings;
+        }
     }
 }
```
</details>

